  "text": "Innovative and application-oriented, refers to the cultivation of talents not based on academic and research-oriented elite education, but on the orientation of popularized education based on technology to meet the actual needs of the vast number of employing units, facing the grass-roots level and the front line of production. Strengthen practical ability and practical ability, pay attention to not only intellectual education, but also the cultivation of non-intelligence factors [CITATION_1] . Innovative talents refer to the fact that the talents trained are wider, more specialized and better able to learn independently than the applied talents trained in higher vocational and technical colleges, and not only have the skills to be competent for a certain occupation, but also have the ability to learn independently. And has applied knowledge to carry on the technical innovation and the technical secondary development ability. Therefore, the cultivation of applied innovative talents must be based on the comprehensive mastery of students' knowledge, take the cultivation of ability as the core, and take the improvement of comprehensive quality as the goal [CITATION_2] .",
